2.00	Horse_hair	Horsehair	Horsehair is the long, coarse hair growing on the manes and tails of horses. It is used for various purposes, including upholstery, brushes, the bows of musical instruments, a hard-wearing fabric called haircloth, and for horsehair plaster, a wallcovering material formerly used in the construction industry and now found only in older buildings.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/eb/Dorsal_stripe_on_a_domestic_horse_IMG_0233.jpg/170px-Dorsal_stripe_on_a_domestic_horse_IMG_0233.jpg
